# Astro Best Practices

## Architecture

- Prefer **static** by default: use server or client directives only when needed.
- Put reusable UI in `src/components/`, layouts in `src/layouts/`, pages in `src/pages/`.
- Use **Astro** for structure and HTML; add **React/Vue/Svelte** only for islands that need interactivity.

## Components & Layouts

- Keep the **frontmatter** (---) at the top; put all imports and logic there.
- Pass content via **slots**; use **named slots** when a layout has multiple regions.
- Prefer **single responsibility**: one layout for shell (html, meta, global styles), pages compose content.

## Performance

- Use **native HTML and CSS** in `.astro` when possible; avoid shipping JS for static content.
- Add `client:load`, `client:idle`, or `client:visible` only on components that must be interactive.
- Prefer **scoped styles** in the component (`<style>`) or global in the layout; avoid duplicate global rules.

## Content & SEO

- Set **title** and **description** (and other meta) in the layout or per-page; use `Astro.props` for dynamic values.
- Use semantic HTML: **header**, **main**, **nav**, **section**, **article**, **footer**.
- External links: use `target="_blank"` with `rel="noopener noreferrer"`.

## Code Style

- Use **kebab-case** for component file names (e.g. `base-layout.astro`).
- Use **PascalCase** for component names in imports and usage.
- Prefer **type-safe props** with TypeScript interfaces in frontmatter.

```astro
---
interface Props {
  title: string;
  description?: string;
}
const { title, description = 'Default' } = Astro.props;
---
```

## Static Site (GitHub Pages)

- Rely on **static build** (`astro build`); no server adapters.
- Put assets in `public/` for unchanged URLs; use `import` for hashed/cached assets.
- Keep **site** and **base** in `astro.config.mjs` correct for deployment (e.g. custom domain or repo path).
